This project uses the React Compiler for automatic memoization and optimization.

## Key Guidelines:

- **DO NOT use `useMemo`, `useCallback`, or `React.memo`** - The React Compiler handles all memoization automatically
- Write simple, readable code without manual optimization attempts
- The compiler will optimize component re-renders and value computations automatically
- Focus on clean component logic rather than performance primitives

## What This Means:

✅ **Do this:**
```javascript
function MyComponent({ items, onSelect }) {
  const filteredItems = items.filter(item => item.active);
  
  const handleClick = (id) => {
    onSelect(id);
  };
  
  return <List items={filteredItems} onClick={handleClick} />;
}
```

❌ **Don't do this:**
```javascript
function MyComponent({ items, onSelect }) {
  const filteredItems = useMemo(
    () => items.filter(item => item.active),
    [items]
  );
  
  const handleClick = useCallback((id) => {
    onSelect(id);
  }, [onSelect]);
  
  return <List items={filteredItems} onClick={handleClick} />;
}
```
